              "id": "s1",
              "text_en": "Rule two. In a massless string, the tension is the same at every point along the string."
            },
            {
              "id": "s2",
              "text_en": "The reason is simple. A massless string needs no extra force to accelerate itself."
            },
            {
              "id": "s3",
              "text_en": "Rule three. Across a massless frictionless pulley, the tension is the same on both sides."
            },
            {
              "id": "s4",
              "text_en": "These three rules together let you treat the tension as a single unknown that lives throughout the string."
            }
          ]
        },
        "advance_mode": "auto_after_tts"
